o so our registration process may require you to provide your name company name address telephone number email address and certain additional information such as for example your preferred contact method and product markets of interest to you collectively “registration data” use of information synchronoss uses registration data to contact you when necessary to respond to your inquiries for additional information to provide additional information according to your preferences and for synchronoss’ other business purposes sometimes registration data is used to send you information about synchronoss and its products services and business partners at your election at any time “optin” you may choose to stop receiving future communications from synchronoss see below sharing of information we are not in the business of selling information about our customers or visitors to our website and currently synchronoss will not share sell rent or trade personal information with any third party for commercial purposes synchronoss may however disclose personal information if  reasonably necessary to perform the service  authorized by you  permitted under this privacy statement or  synchronoss is required to do so by law or regulation or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to i conform or comply with any legal regulatory law enforcement bankruptcy proceedings or similar requirement or investigation ii protect or defend the rights or property of synchronoss or any other user or iii enforce the terms of use that are applicable to the service if synchronoss is involved in a merger acquisition or sale of all or a portion of its assets you will be notified via email andor a prominent notice on our web site of any change in ownership or uses of your personal information as well as any choices you may have regarding your personal information in the event we so disclose personal information to third parties we require these third parties to use your personal information only as necessary to help us perform the service synchronoss may transfer traffic data and registration data including personal information to any successor to all or substantially all of its business or assets that concerns the service we will share your personal information with third parties only in the ways that are described in this privacy policy security the security of your personal information is important to us we follow generally accepted standards to protect the personal information submitted to us both during transmission and once we receive it information collected by synchronoss is stored in secure operating environments that are not made generally available to the public unfortunately no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed to be  secure as a result synchronoss cannot ensure the security of any information you provide and you do so at your own risk once synchronoss receives your transmission it will make reasonable efforts to ensure its security on its systems third party sites the service may permit you to link to other websites on the internet and other websites may contain links to the site these other websites are not under synchronoss’ control the privacy and security practices of websites linked to or from the site are not covered by this privacy statement and synchronoss is not responsible for the privacy or security practices or the content of such websites tracking technologies as is true of most web sites we gather certain information automatically and store it in log files this information may include internet protocol ip addresses browser type internet service provider isp referringexit pages operating system datetime stamp andor clickstream data to analyze trends in the aggregate and administer the site we do not link this automatically collected data to other information we collect about you synchronoss and google analytics which is our marketing analytics service provider and youtube for video hosting and addthis for content sharing use cookies or similar technologies in analyzing trends administering the site tracking users’ movements around the site and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole we may request reports based on the use of these technologies by our marketing analytics service provider partners on an individual as well as aggregated basis we use cookies for marketing analytics users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level if you reject cookies you may still use our site but your ability to use some features or areas of our site may be limited behavioral targeting retargeting our third party partner may use technologies such as cookies to gather information about your activities on this site and other sites in order to provide you advertising based upon your browsing activities and interests if you wish to not have this information used for the purpose of serving you interestbased ads you may optout by clicking here or if located in the european union click here please note this does not opt you out of being served ads you will continue to receive generic ads service providers we use other third parties to provide services on our site such as for site hosting investor relations and widgets our site may be framed within a service providers site we will share your personal information as necessary for the third party to provide that service these third parties are prohibited from using your personal information for any other purpose user access and choice you may elect to avoid future communications from synchronoss by sending an email to optoutsynchronosscom that includes your electronic mail address provided synchronoss reserves the right to use your contact information to send you important information such as for example information about products and services that you have acquired from synchronoss or information about changes to this privacy statement upon request synchronoss will provide you with information about whether we hold any of your personal information if you wish to have access and correct update or delete inaccurate data please contact us we will respond within  days to your inquiry data retention we will retain your information as needed to provide you services we will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations resolve disputes and enforce our agreements blogs and testimonials if you use a bulletin board or blog on this web site you should be aware that any personal information you submit there can be read collected or used by other users of these forums and could be used to send you unsolicited messages we are not responsible for the personal information you choose to submit in these forums to request removal of your personal information from our blog or forum please contact us in some cases we may not be able to remove your personal information in which case we will let you know if we are unable to do so and why we also have testimonials on our site which display personal information the individuals who have provided these testimonials have given permission to have their personal information and testimonial displayed if you wish to update or delete your testimonial you can contact us widgets widgets support functions that require that you disclose certain personal information given the user’s choice of participation this information is collected in many different ways such as forms surveys contests forums subscribing or unsubscribing to mailings and correcting or updating personal information and are only used for the purpose in which they were collected our web site includes social media features such as the facebook like button and widgets such as the share this button or interactive miniprograms that run on our site these features may collect your ip address which page you are visiting on our site and may set a cookie to enable the feature to function properly social media features and widgets are either hosted by a third party or hosted directly on our site your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy of the company providing it nonus users you expressly consent to synchronoss’ processing of your personal information in accordance with this privacy statement your personal information may be processed by synchronoss in the country where it was collected and in the united states united states laws regarding processing of personal information may be less stringent than the laws in your country if you represent an organization you will ensure that each member of your organization including employees and contractors about whom personal information may be provided to synchronoss has given his or her express consent to synchronoss’ processing of such personal information condition of use and revisions if you choose to visit the site your visit and any dispute over privacy is subject to this privacy statement as governed by the laws of the state of new jersey if we decide to change our privacy policy we will post those changes to this privacy statement the home page and other places we deem appropriate so that you are aware of what information we collect how we use it and under what circumstances if any we disclose it information collected by the service is subject to the privacy statement in effect at the time of use you may correct or otherwise change your registration data by contacting synchronoss as provided below we reserve the right to modify this privacy statement at any time so please review it frequently if we make material changes to this policy we will notify you here or by means of a notice on our home page prior to the change becoming effective if you have an unresolved privacy or data use concern that we have not addressed satisfactorily please contact our usbased third party dispute resolution provider free of charge at httpsfeedbackformtrustecomwatchdogrequest us – swiss safe harbor framework synchronoss technologies inc complies with the the us – swiss safe harbor framework as set forth by the us department of commerce regarding the collection use and retention of personal information from switzerland synchronoss technologies inc has certified that it adheres to the safe harbor privacy principles of notice choice onward transfer security data integrity access and enforcement to learn more about the safe harbor program and to view synchronoss technologies inc’s certification please visit httpssafeharborexportgovswisslistaspx customers suppliers and industry partners synchronoss may obtain various types of eu and swiss personal information about employees and agents of our customers suppliers and industry partners such data may include contact information such as names addresses phone and fax numbers and email addresses information about products and services ordered or provided and information collected related to gauge interest in internetbased ecommerce capabilities or provide technical literature or product demos synchronoss may use these types of eu and swiss personal information for business purposes including to deliver information related to our products or services to establish or maintain client and business relationships to provide access to documentation related to synchronoss’ internetbased and ecommerce activities and to conduct other activities related to managing business relationships as necessary or appropriate in connection with the servicing and development of the business relationship employees and agents of our clients industry partners and suppliers may contact us if any of their eu and swiss personal information changes or if they would like to access and correct eu and swiss personal information that we maintain about them in any event such persons can also contact us by sending an email to legalsynchronosscom or by using the information at the end of this privacy statement consumers synchronoss provides a wide variety of services and solutions to its business clients “clients” that facilitate services related to the online provisioning and activation of network and homebased services synchronoss develops systems to interface with our clients’ online order capture systems and receives information for each order about the individual that placed the order “consumer” in all instances synchronoss will obtain access to eu and swiss personal information about such consumers in the course of fulfilling the order and or services offered on our customer’s web site such data may include name address phone bank account number social security number credit status email address credit or bank card number billing history and other information depending on the particular client and application at issue we also supplement data such as credit verification status and address validation services wherever we obtain access to eu and swiss personal information about data subjects or end users we are acting as a mere data processor on behalf of our clients and we therefore conduct such activities strictly in accordance with their instructions and pursuant to our contractual arrangements with them if you are an end user consumer with an existing relationship with one of our clients you should refer to the client’s website to understand the privacy practices that apply to eu and swiss personal information that we may maintain about you moreover if you would like to access and review your eu and swiss personal information you should contact our client with any such requests we will cooperate as appropriate with requests from our clients to assist with such responses other necessary disclosures synchronoss may disclose eu and swiss personal information to business partners and subcontractors as necessary in connection with the performance of requested services or solutions or as otherwise appropriate in connection with a legitimate business need services that integrate with our systems that are directly related to the fulfillment of the consumers order may include device insurance providers third party logistics providers wireless wireline and cable service providers mobile device management providers merchant banks credit verification services address validation services and website analytics providers synchronoss may also disclose eu and swiss personal information as necessary in connection with the sale or transfer of all or part of the business in these situations synchronoss will require the recipient of the data to protect the data in accordance with the relevant principles in the safe harbors or otherwise take steps to ensure that the eu and swiss personal information is appropriately protected synchronoss may also disclose eu and swiss personal information where required or permitted by law or where synchronoss believes that such disclosures are appropriate in connection with a law enforcement request data security and integrity synchronoss has global hosting centers that store and process eu and swiss personal information in various locations in the united states and the eu synchronoss takes reasonable precautions to protect eu and swiss personal information in these centers and in other locations in the united states from loss misuse and unauthorized access disclosure alteration and destruction synchronoss also makes reasonable efforts to keep eu and swiss personal information reliable for its intended use accurate current and complete synchronoss technologies inc if you have any questions regarding this privacy statement or your dealings at this site or a request to correct or delete personal information please contact synchronoss at synchronoss technologies inc attn privacy statement  crossing boulevard th floor bridgewater nj  tel   contact us we will use commercially reasonable efforts to fulfill your request in a timely manner last updated january    synchronoss technologies inc   tip from  visitors foursquarelog insign upnearbyget inspiredtop pickstrendingfoodcoffeenightlifefunshoppingplanning a trip to new yorkfoursq